### Get all users
GET http://localhost:8080/users
Accept: application/json

### Create a new user
POST http://localhost:8080/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "password123",
  "email": "testuser@example.com"
}

### Get user by ID (replace {id} with an actual ID)
GET http://localhost:8080/users/1
Accept: application/json

### Update user (replace {id} with an actual ID)
PUT http://localhost:8080/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "updateduser",
  "password": "newpassword123",
  "email": "updated@example.com"
}

### Delete user (replace {id} with an actual ID)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/users/1

### Search users by username pattern
GET http://localhost:8080/users/search?username=test
Accept: application/json

### Get user by username
GET http://localhost:8080/users/username/testuser
Accept: application/json

### Get user by email
GET http://localhost:8080/users/email?email=testuser@example.com
Accept: application/json